name: jupyterhub-ldapauthenticator
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jupyterhub-ldapauthenticator" %}
{% set version = "1.3.2" %}
{% set sha256 = "758081bbdb28b26313bb18c9d8aa2b8fcdc9162e4d3ab196c626567e64f1ab8b" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.5
    - pip
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python >=3.5
    - jupyterhub
    - ldap3
    - tornado
    - traitlets

test:
  imports:
    - ldapauthenticator

about:
  home: https://github.com/jupyterhub/ldapauthenticator
  license: BSD-3
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: LDAP Authenticator for JupyterHub

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - dhirschfeld
    - minrk
    - consideRatio
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
